name: Brian Wilson
summary: Due to recent concerns about his well-being following the death of his wife, a conservatorship has been approved for Beach Boys legend Brian Wilson, now 81. This legal arrangement grants Wilson's daughters the authority to oversee his personal and financial matters. The decision stemmed from a medical evaluation that indicated Wilson's diminished capacity, particularly with regard to dementia. Multiple news outlets, including Variety, The Associated Press, USA TODAY, Rolling Stone, Fox News, The Daily Beast, PEOPLE, WDSU New Orleans, Daily Mail, and Ultimate Classic Rock, have reported on this development.

name: Brain worms
summary: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. (RFK Jr.) recently disclosed that he has been suffering from a parasitic worm infection in his brain. The worm, identified as a pork tapeworm (Taenia solium), is a type of flatworm that can infect humans through the consumption of undercooked pork. In RFK Jr.'s case, it is believed that the worm entered his brain through his sinuses. The infection has reportedly caused Kennedy to experience a range of symptoms, including seizures and cognitive difficulties. While brain worm infections are rare, they are a potentially serious health issue that can lead to long-term neurological complications. Treatment typically involves medication to kill the worm and surgery to remove it from the brain. RFK Jr.'s case has raised concerns about the potential for brain worm infections in the United States, as well as the importance of proper food safety practices to prevent such infections.

name: Jimmy Johnson
summary: Pro Football Hall of Famer Jimmy Johnson, a legendary cornerback who spent his entire 16-season NFL career with the San Francisco 49ers, has passed away at the age of 86. Johnson, who was inducted into the Hall of Fame in 1994, was a key member of the 49ers' dynasty of the 1980s and 1990s. During his time with the team, he won three Super Bowls and was named to eight Pro Bowls. Johnson's exceptional athleticism and defensive prowess made him one of the most respected players of his era, and his passing has left a void in the football community.

name: Frank Vogel
summary: The Phoenix Suns have fired head coach Frank Vogel after just one season at the helm, following the team's disappointing first-round playoff sweep by the Minnesota Timberwolves. The Suns are reportedly eyeing Mike Budenholzer, former head coach of the Atlanta Hawks, as Vogel's replacement. While some sources indicated that the Suns considered retaining Vogel but overhauling his coaching staff, the team ultimately decided to part ways with him. The Suns' firing of Vogel comes after a season that fell short of expectations, with the team failing to build on its success from the previous season when they reached the NBA Finals.
